com.navis.framework.portal.query

Class NullDomainQuery

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.navis.framework.portal.query.NullDomainQuery
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MetaFilter, DataQuery, DomainQuery, BasicQuery, Bounded, ExecutableQuery, Ordered, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class NullDomainQuery
extends java.lang.Object
implements DomainQuery
    Equivalent to NullDataQuery, intended for ZkPrimaryQueryTableModel compatibility

    This is a wrapper for DomainQueryImpl. It provides all access for callers responsible for configuring this query. However, when a query processor is selected based on instance type tests, it will appear to be a null query and won't be executed, as required by current convention. At any point, the delegate domain query can be retrieved and used normally where appropriate.

    Note: For internal framework use only.

    See Also:
